        public FractionImpl​(int numerator,
                    int denominator)

        Creates a fraction given the numerator and denominator. Fraction will be normalised to lowest terms with Euclid's algorithm.
        Parameters:

        denominator - the denominator.

        java.lang.ArithmeticException - if denominator is zero.

      • FractionImpl

        public FractionImpl​(java.lang.String fraction)
             throws java.lang.ArithmeticException,
                    java.lang.NumberFormatException
        Creates a fraction from a String, with the format "numerator/denominator" or is a whole number. Fraction will be normalised to lowest terms with Euclid's algorithm.
        Parameters:
        fraction - the fraction (or whole number) as a String.
        Throws:
        java.lang.ArithmeticException - if denominator is zero.
        java.lang.NumberFormatException - if fraction is malformed.
